In some embodiments, the first model may be a depth residual network (deep residual network, resNet). The server can obtain the video feature vector based on ResNet, and ResNet can effectively improve the accuracy of model training in the process of increasing the network depth. Specifically, in the embodiment of the present application, the video to be processed is taken as an example of N selected images. The application can also obtain video feature vectors through other network models, which is not limited.
The server may input the N images into Resnet, and the Resnet may include at least one convolutional layer for extracting features of the input data and at least one pooling layer for sampling the input data. Both the convolution layer and the pooling layer include an activation function.
In an embodiment of the present application, a convolution layer may be used to extract initial features of the N input images. Specifically, in the first step, N images are subjected to vector conversion to obtain N image vectors, where the N image vectors may be combined into an image vector matrix. And secondly, inputting the image vector matrix into a convolution layer, and performing convolution operation on the image vector matrix by using a convolution kernel, namely performing inner product operation on the image vector matrix and the convolution kernel to obtain a convolution result corresponding to the image vector matrix. Next, the convolution result is non-linearly transformed based on the activation function and a bias vector is added to obtain an initial feature vector. And thirdly, inputting the initial feature vector into a pooling layer, and performing feature sampling on the initial feature vector. Then, the convolution result is subjected to nonlinear transformation based on the activation function, and a bias vector is added to obtain a video feature vector.
And S602, extracting features from the text to be processed by the server to obtain text feature vectors, wherein the text to be processed corresponds to the video to be processed.
In the embodiment of the application, the text to be processed comprises at least one of theme information, title information, subtitle information and classification information of the video to be processed.
For how to obtain the text feature vector, reference may be made to the description of how to obtain the text feature vector from the sample video in the first embodiment, which is not repeated here.
The training method of the second model may be referred to the related description in the first embodiment, and will not be repeated here.
The second model is used to extract features of the input data, and in embodiments of the present application, the second model is used to extract features of the sample text. The method for obtaining the text feature vector from the second model may refer to the method for obtaining the video feature vector from the first model in S601, which is not described herein. In the embodiment of the present application, the second model may be a bidirectional attention neural network model (bidirectional encoder representation from transformers, BERT), or may be another network model, which is not limited in this respect by the present application.
And S603, the server splices the text feature vector and the video feature vector to obtain a multi-mode feature vector.
In some embodiments, the text to be processed includes a text corresponding to a text feature vector, and the video feature vector includes N image feature vectors. N image feature vectors can be spliced with text feature vectors in sequence respectively, and one row or one column of the obtained multi-mode feature vectors comprises one image feature vector and one text feature vector.
